  "description": "Kentucky voters will elect one U.S. senator in 2026. The race is open because incumbent Mitch McConnell announced he will not seek re-election, making this one of the cycle\u2019s notable open-seat Senate contests. Kentucky has leaned strongly Republican in recent federal elections, but the GOP primary is competitive and has drawn attention because candidates are competing to define themselves as aligned with or distinct from McConnell and President Trump. The general election is expected to be shaped by Kentucky\u2019s partisan lean, the open-seat dynamic, and contrasts over ideology, governing style, and national Republican politics.",
